The paper deals with the problem of domain shift in image classification, which is a common issue in computer vision (cs.CV). The authors propose a method for learning transform-based domain adaptation classifiers, which involves optimization techniques and machine learning algorithms (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of large-scale internet image collections, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper involves experiments and evaluations of the proposed method, which can be considered as information retrieval (cs.IR).
